original: Eliason, Gustav Axel, disponent, Fritsla, f. 15/3/87 i Kinna, Älvsb. 1., av Elias Andersson o. Edela Jönsson. G. 23 m. Eleonora Persson. Barn: Ingemar f. 25, Birgit 28. — Res. t. Holl., Belg. o. Tyskl. f. stud. av lant-br., disp. f. A-B Sv. Wellpappfabr. i Kinnahult sed. 30. Deläg. o. styr:-led. där sed. s. å.
translated: Eliason, Gustav Axel, manager, Fritsla, born March 15, 1887 in Kinna, Älvsborg County, son of Elias Andersson and Edela Jönsson. Married on the 23rd of a month (not specified) to Eleonora Persson. Children: Ingemar (born) in 1925, Birgit (born) in 1928. Studied agriculture in Holland, Belgium, and Germany and worked as a manager for A-B Swedish Corrugated cardboard factory in Kinnahult since 1930. Became a partial owner and board member of the company the same year.
